properties.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued February 7 at 7:45PM EST until February 7 at 9:00PM EST by NWS Baltimore MD/Washington DC
properties.description:
* WHAT...Up to one foot of inundation above ground level in low
lying areas due to tidal flooding.

* WHERE...Shoreline in Southern Baltimore County and the city of
Baltimore.

* WHEN...Until 9 PM EST this evening.

* IMPACTS...At 3.0 feet, water begins encroaching upon yards in
the Bowleys Quarters area.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Tides one and a half to two feet above
normal. High tide is ongoing in the Bowley's Quarters area.
properties.instruction:
If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be
closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of
unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone
property.

NWSheadline: COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM EST THIS EVENING
